    {
      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "**<strong>**\n\n**<strong>**\n\n**[A bright, slightly too-loudly cheerful medical-themed aesthetic. Think overly vibrant scrubs and a desk that looks like it was decorated by a motivational poster company.]**\n\n**[SCENE START]**\n\n**INT. DOCTOR'S OFFICE - DAY**\n\nDR. QUARK (40s, impeccably dressed in slightly too-tight, brightly colored scrubs. He possesses an almost cartoonish, over-the-top confidence. He leans back in his chair, one leg crossed over the other, radiating effortless self-assurance.)\n\nA nervous PATIENT (30s-50s, visibly uncomfortable, clutching their chest slightly) sits opposite him.\n\nDR. QUARK\n(Waving a dismissive hand, a wide, confident grin plastered on his face)\nNow, now, hold your horses there, friend. \"Tightness,\" \"burning,\" \"arm thing\"... sounds like a classic case of the modern man's digestive drama.\n\nThe Patient shifts uncomfortably, trying to articulate the severity of the pain.\n\nDR. QUARK (CONT'D)\n(Leaning forward conspiratorially, but with zero genuine concern)",
