    {
      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "[SCENE START]\n\n**INT. DOCTOR'S OFFICE - DAY**\n\nThe office is overly bright, perhaps a little too vibrant. DR. QUARK (40s, impeccably dressed in slightly too-tight scrubs, radiating unwarranted confidence) leans back in his chair, one leg crossed over the other. He has a practiced, breezy smirk.\n\nPATIENT (M/F, mid-40s, visibly uncomfortable, clutching their chest) sits opposite him, looking genuinely worried.\n\nDR. QUARK\n(Waving a dismissive hand, a theatrical flourish)\nNow, now, hold your horses there, friend. \"Chest tightness,\" \"arm radiating\"—sounds like a bit of a dramatic performance, doesn't it?\n\nThe Patient shifts uncomfortably, trying to articulate the severity of the pain.\n\nDR. QUARK (CONT'D)\n(Chuckles, a loud, confident sound)\nLook, I hear you. Heartburn, right? Classic. The stomach throwing a little tantrum. And that little twinge down the arm? Probably just nerves playing dress-up.\n\nHe leans forward conspiratorially, but his tone is entirely patronizing.\n\nDR",
